You only need to learn three notes to play "Mary Had a Little Lamb". Those notes are B, A and G. Practice playing each of these notes individually before you start working on the song. Play B: B is the first note most people learn on the recorder, as it is one of the easiest to play. To play a B note, use your left thumb to cover the hole on the back of the recorder and use your left index finger to cover the first or top hole on the front of the recorder. Make sure to completely cover both holes with your fingers. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/88\/Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-2.jpg\/v4-459px-Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/88\/Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-2.jpg\/v4-759px-Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Play A: To play A, use your left thumb to cover the hole on the back of the recorder, your left index finger to cover the first hole on the front of the recorder and your left middle finger to cover the second hole. It's basically the same as B, just with one extra finger. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/10\/Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-3.jpg\/v4-459px-Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/10\/Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-3.jpg\/v4-759px-Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Play G: To play G, use your left thumb to cover the hole on the back of the recorder, your left index finger to cover the first hole on the front of the recorder, your left middle finger to cover the second hole and your left ring finger to cover the third hole. It's basically the same as A, just with one extra finger. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/19\/Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-5.jpg\/v4-459px-Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-5.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/19\/Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-5.jpg\/v4-759px-Play-%22Mary-Had-a-Little-Lamb%22-on-the-Recorder-Step-5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}
